page.title: 03Painswick Elections
page.content: The Gloucestershire County Council elections were held on 5th May 1985. The polling stations were open from 8am-9pm.The votes were then counted in Stratford Park leisure centre. Our 'D' block consists of one County Council district,Painswick.The S.D.P. and the Conservative party were the only parties represented.The turn out was 50% of the electorate voting. The result was that the Conservative coucillor for the last 7 years lost to Graham Marshall (S.D.P) standing for the first time.The votes were S.D.P. 1676,and Conservatives 1666,votes.This swing to the centre occured in several places in the county and this led to a council in which no party had overall control.S.D.P. Liberal Alliance 23 seats,Conservative and right wing independents 23 seats,Labour 14 seats, others 3 seats.
